<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4129] C++ TNonblockingServer fd leak when failing to dispatch new connections</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4129</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2789&quot; title=&quot;TNonblockingServer leaks socket FD&amp;#39;s under load&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-2789&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-2789&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the error handling for connections where notify fails leaks a file descriptor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was reported and fixed in a pull request without an Apache Jira entry:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1210/files&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1210/files&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When failing to dispatch new connections to other IO threads other&lt;br/&gt;
than the number 0, we returned these connections for reuse without&lt;br/&gt;
closing them, so the corresponding fds were leaked forever.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should close these connections instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
